    "long_instructions": "#Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Add a painter object\r\n#\r\n- Add methods to paint a line to the cone\r\n\t- **Hint:** Use your pseudocode on the Activity Guide for task 1: A to E\r\n#\r\n- **Discuss:** How does your pseudocode compare to the Python code needed? \r\n\t- What is the same?\r\n\t- What is different?\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: black;\">\r\n<i class=\"fa-duotone fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <strong>Methods</strong> \r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nUse these methods to use with the painter object:    \r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n`painter.move()`\r\n\r\n`painter.turn_left()`  \r\n\r\n`painter.take_paint()`\r\n\r\n`painter.paint(\"color\")`",
